&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Intern&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Description of you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Marketing Intern&lt;/strong&gt; to join the TitanApps marketing team and own our Link Building &amp;amp; Outreach direction. This is a hands-on, execution-focused role with a clear mission: increase TitanApps’s visibility in LLMs, build high-quality backlinks, and drive measurable results in SEO &amp;amp; GEO.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you&#39;re passionate about SEO, enjoy building relationships with relevant websites, crafting outreach campaigns that get responses, and seeing high-quality backlinks go live, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your skills&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Genuine interest in outreach/SEO: &lt;/strong&gt;You’re comfortable with repetitive, detail-heavy work and energized by the hunt for the right opportunity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advanced English&lt;/strong&gt; skills, both written and spoken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Self-organization: &lt;/strong&gt;You can manage multiple active conversations, track progress across many threads, and hit deadlines without someone checking in on you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-tool fluency: &lt;/strong&gt;You already use ChatGPT, Claude, or similar tools for research and content generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Good at finding things online: &lt;/strong&gt;You know how to find information and contacts online: LinkedIn, social media, direct channels. You don’t stop at the first dead end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comfort with basic IT tools: &lt;/strong&gt;Google Suite, project management tools.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Would be a plus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical marketing exposure: &lt;/strong&gt;Familiarity with cold email infrastructure, automation tools, or SEO basics. You’re willing to go deeper here.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience with SaaS or B2B products: &lt;/strong&gt;You understand how product-led growth works and why backlinks to a SaaS product matter beyond raw traffic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prior outreach experience: &lt;/strong&gt;Even personal projects, freelance gigs, or academic work counts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research &amp;amp; identify opportunities: &lt;/strong&gt;Find high-quality websites, blogs, and publications for link building. You know where to look and how to evaluate what’s worth pursuing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run outreach campaigns: &lt;/strong&gt;Execute email and social outreach to secure backlinks and guest posting placements. Own the full cycle,&amp;nbsp; from first contact to confirmation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build relationships: &lt;/strong&gt;Nurture connections with bloggers, journalists, and content creators in relevant niches.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay sharp on SEO &amp;amp; LLMs: &lt;/strong&gt;Actively learn and apply knowledge on SEO fundamentals and LLM optimization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate across teams: &lt;/strong&gt;Work with our marketing and content teams to align outreach activities with broader marketing goals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Track everything: &lt;/strong&gt;Maintain organized records of outreach efforts, responses, and acquired links in tracking spreadsheets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a QA Engineer who cares about product quality end-to-end. You’ll work on Coupler.io — a no-code data integration and analytics platform that provides instant access to 400+ sources and processes millions of records daily, helping ensure its reliability, accuracy, and smooth integrations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll focus on how the product works in real conditions: testing integrations, investigating edge cases, and resolving complex issues together with engineering, product, and support teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What are we looking for?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing &amp;amp; QA expertise:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with manual testing and end-to-end validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in investigating customer issues and performing root cause analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in API testing (working with docs + real behavior, identifying inconsistencies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in building and improving QA processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong debugging and problem-solving skills, including log analysis (CloudWatch, Logs Explorer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of networks, HTTP, APIs, and web/client architectures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with version control systems (GitHub, GitLab, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using AI tools for workflow optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; mindset:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate technical concepts for different audiences (engineering ↔ non-technical)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sense of ownership and accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structured, detail-oriented approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English (written and spoken)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Would be a plus&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Playwright (TypeScript)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze requirements, test functionality, and identify defects and edge cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own investigation of complex customer issues through L3 support, driving root cause resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate third-party API integrations across testing and production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with engineering and product to resolve issues and improve system reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve QA practices and elevate debugging and investigation standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support releases and ensure stable rollouts with active post-release follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Description of you&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to join Coupler.io, a data integration platform used by marketers, analysts, and ops teams at 200k companies worldwide.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re someone who genuinely enjoys understanding how businesses work, building trust with clients, and helping people get real value from a product they use every day, this role is for you. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ll lead live demos, guide clients through onboarding, grow existing accounts, and work closely with teams across marketing, product, and customer success to make sure every client interaction counts. If this sounds like a great fit, we’d love to receive your CV!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;*This role is open for CET-aligned hours: 8:00 AM–5:00 PM or 3:00 PM–11:00 PM. Please apply only if you can commit to one of these windows.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your skills&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2+ year&lt;/strong&gt; in sales, account management, or customer success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience with live demos and discovery calls.&lt;/strong&gt; You can run a product walkthrough, handle objections, and move deals forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with &lt;strong&gt;SaaS contracts&lt;/strong&gt; with an average value of &lt;strong&gt;$5K+ per year&lt;/strong&gt;. You understand how B2B deals are structured and what drives renewals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fluent English&lt;/strong&gt;, written and spoken.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CRM experience.&lt;/strong&gt; You use it to manage pipeline, not just to report on it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech-savvy and a fast learner.&lt;/strong&gt; You can get up to speed on a complex product and explain it clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical and consultative mindset. &lt;/strong&gt;You listen carefully, identify the real problem behind a request, and recommend solutions that actually fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comfortable managing multiple priorities&lt;/strong&gt; — open deals, active accounts, and partner conversations at the same time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Would be a plus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of data analytics or reporting tools (Google Sheets, Looker Studio, Power BI, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of marketing tools, workflows, or MarTech platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with or selling to marketing agencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Coupler.io or similar data integration tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run live demos.&lt;/strong&gt; This is the core of the role — expect 70%+ of your time on calls with prospective and new clients, guiding them from first touchpoint to product adoption and multi-year contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Convert inbound leads into paying customers.&lt;/strong&gt; Manage the full inbound sales cycle: qualify, demo, follow up, negotiate, and close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow revenue from existing accounts.&lt;/strong&gt; Identify upsell opportunities, expand usage within accounts, and convert annual contracts into multi-year commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage solution partners and resellers.&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain relationships with strategic partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own account health end-to-end.&lt;/strong&gt; Help clients get genuine, ongoing value from the product, connect them with new features, optimize their setup, and stay ahead of their evolving needs.&lt;/li&gt;
